# Trivy CVE exclusions for cc-fe.
#
# Add entries sparingly. Each entry MUST have a comment explaining:
#   1. Why this CVE doesn't apply to our build (false positive justification).
#   2. What we'd need to change to remove the entry.
#
# Format: <CVE-ID> followed by a blank line, comments above only.
# An optional ` exp:YYYY-MM-DD` suffix sets an auto-expiry.

# ----- picomatch ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns -----
# Status: false positive on declarative metadata.
# yarn.lock pins picomatch to 4.0.4 (see "resolutions" in package.json),
# and yarn install verifies this. Trivy still flags 4.0.3 because some
# transitive dep's package.json declares "^4.0.3" as its requirement
# string in dist/<app>/server/package.json — but at install time, yarn's
# resolution wins and only 4.0.4 is actually installed. The vulnerable
# 4.0.3 code is never present at runtime.
# Remove when: every transitive dep that declares "^4.0.3" publishes a
# new version declaring "^4.0.4" (track via Renovate PRs).
CVE-2026-33671
